# Backup schedule, installed on the production server during OPS-001 —
# Server Provisioning.
#
# Reference: docs/01-architecture/ARCH-008-backup-architecture.md, Section 5
#            docs/04-operations/OPS-004-backup.md

# Daily full backup run at 03:00 UTC (low-traffic window).
#
# Path note: run-backup.sh lives at /srv/platform/backup/, the synced
# runtime copy of infrastructure/backup/ (see OPS-011 and ARCH-002,
# Section 10 — Directory Mapping), not the working clone used at
# provisioning time. This file itself is installed as the deploy user's
# crontab by infrastructure/automation/deploy-component.sh.
0 3 * * * /srv/platform/backup/run-backup.sh >> /var/log/platform-backup.log 2>&1
